                      NPC Behavior: Wander Behavior
                      =============================

Description
-----------

The set_wander functionality in monster.c has been subsumed by the
generic wander behavior.

The NPC can be set with both a wander % chance and a delay between
wander attempts. Additionally, the NPC can be set to wander only
in particular terrains (as defined in <terrain.h>) or in rooms with
filenames that begine with a particular prefix (eg. /players/malraux)
in order to restrict wandering NPCs to certain areas.

NPC Wander API
-------------

varargs void set_wander(int move_chance, int move_delay, int state)
- Enable the NPC for wandering with the specified chance, delay, and
  state settings. Chance defaults to 5%, and delay defaults to 15
  seconds. State defaults to NS_RESTING.
  You must also include <npcstate.h> when using NS_RESTING.

void set_wander_terrains(int terrains)
- Restrict the NPC to wandering only in rooms of the specified
  terrains. Default is TER_ALL if this function is never called.

void set_wander_chance(int chance)
- Set the % chance for the NPC to wander.

void set_wander_delay(int delay)
- Sets the time in seconds between wander % chance checks.

void set_wander_prefix(string prefix)
- Sets the prefix to compare potential rooms against. If this is
  set, the NPC will not enter rooms with filenames that don't
  begin with the prefix. For example, setting the prefix to
  /players/malraux/room/village would restrict the NPC to rooms
  in that area only.

object query_wander_behavior()
- Return the wander behavior object for further customization.


NPC Wander Behavior API
---------------------

The wander behavior object can also be manipulated directly:

void set_terrains(int terrains)
- Restrict the NPC to wandering only in rooms of the specified
  terrains. Default is TER_ALL if this function is never called.

void set_chance(int chance)
- Set the % chance for the NPC to wander.

void set_delay(int delay)
- Sets the time in seconds between wander % chance checks.

void set_prefix(string prefix)
- Sets the prefix to compare potential rooms against. If this is
  set, the NPC will not enter rooms with filenames that don't
  begin with the prefix. For example, setting the prefix to
  /players/malraux/room/village would restrict the NPC to rooms
  in that area only.

void set_command(string command)
- Sets a command to prefix to the exit direction when wandering.
  Example: set_command("step") will make the NPC execute
  "step east" instead of "east". Useful for riding NPCs, NPCs
  using movement objects (like the 7 League boots), etc.



